      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, Royal Botanic Garden, ¶ The Melbourne Botanic Gardens did not obtainaRoyal Charter until 1958. ¶ 26 September 1864. ¶ Esteemed Professor, ¶  ¶ It is not very long since I sent you a case wi...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">64.09.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Johan Areschoug</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">J. E. Areschoug brefsamling, Kungl. Vetenskapsakademien, Stockholm.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne, im königl. bot Garten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">am 26 Sept. 1864</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Verehrter Herr Professor.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es ist nicht gar lange seit eine Kiste mit Algen durch meine Agenten, Messrs Betham &amp; Blackitt an Sie absandte und nun liegen bereits wieder eine Menge für Sie bereit, die bald befördert werden sollen. Ich möchte Sie bitten, Ihren Landsmann Herrn Prof. Agardh an der Vertheilung der Pflanzen Antheil nehmen zu lassen, damit er die Species in seinem Werke berücksichtige. Es trifft diesen Gelehrten der Vorwurf in seinem sonst vortrefflichen Algenwerk die Quelle der Literatur nicht erschöpft zu haben, so z. B. würde er eine grosse Anzahl Standorte habe entnehmen können aus den Abhandlungen des Hr Dr Sonder über meine Tange in der Linnaea.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochachtungsvoll</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Vielleicht liegt dem Professor Agardh daran mit meiner Anstalt in directen Verkehr zu treten. Ich habe gerade ein Werk über die Vegetation der Chatham Inseln (nahe Neu-Seeland) vollendet u <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>werde die Ehre haben Ihnen selbige darzubieten.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, Royal Botanic Garden,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Melbourne Botanic Gardens did not obtain<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Royal Charter until 1958.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26 September 1864.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Esteemed Professor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is not very long since I sent you a case with algae through my<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>agents, Messrs Betham &amp; Blackitt,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Blackith.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See M to J. Areschoug, 25 May 1864<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 64-05-25a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and now a lot are already lying ready for you, soon to be transmitted. I would like to ask you to let your compatriot Professor Agardh receive part of the distribution, so that he can take the species into consideration in his work. This scholar has been accused that in his otherwise excellent algological work<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Agardh (1848-80)?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he did not exhaust the literary resources; thus, for instance, he could have extracted a large number of locality records from Dr Sonder's papers on my seaweeds in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Linnaea</seg>.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sonder (1852),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sonder (1853a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Professor Agardh may perhaps be interested to enter into direct communication with my Institute. I have just completed a work on the vegetation of the Chatham Islands<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B64.10.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(near New Zealand) and shall have the honour to present you with a copy.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
